def: In the manner of a hag.

Any one of numerous species of long, slender Alcyonariabelonging to Virgularia and allied genera of the family Virgularidæ.These corals are allied to the sea-pens, but have a long rodlikerhachis inclosing a slender, round or square, calcareous axis. Thepolyps are arranged in transverse rows or clusters along each side ofthe rhachis.

Originally, denoting that the element to the name of which itis prefixed in the respective compounds exercised its highestvalence; now, only that the element has a higher valence than inother similar compounds; thus, barium peroxide is the highest oxideof barium; while nitrogen and manganese peroxides, so-called, are notthe highest oxides of those elements.
An evening party; -- distinguished from levee, and matinée.
Something not true; a false statement. [Recent & R.] A.Trollope.
The quality or state of being watery; moisture; humidity.
At or belonging to an apex, tip, or summit. Gray.
To utter with a musical or prolonged note or tone; to chant;as, to intone the church service.
